# Sports API - Sample HTTP Requests
# Use this file with REST Client extensions in VS Code or similar tools

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5287
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check (if implemented)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Get all clients
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients

### Get client by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/clients/1

### Create a new client - Nike
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/clients
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Nike",
  "description": "Global sports brand and footwear company"
}

### Create a new client - Hurley
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/clients
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Hurley",
  "description": "Premium surf and beach lifestyle brand"
}

### Update a client
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/clients/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Nike Inc.",
  "description": "Global leader in athletic footwear and apparel"
}

### Delete a client
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/clients/999

### Get all campaigns
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/campaigns

### Get campaign by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/campaigns/1

### Create a new campaign
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/campaigns
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Summer 2026 Collection",
  "description": "New summer sports apparel and footwear line",
  "startDate": "2026-06-01T00:00:00Z",
  "endDate": "2026-08-31T23:59:59Z",
  "targetAudience": "Athletes and fitness enthusiasts aged 18-35",
  "budget": 500000.00,
  "clientId": 1
}

### Update a campaign
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/campaigns/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "budget": 550000.00,
  "endDate": "2026-09-15T23:59:59Z"
}

### Delete a campaign
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/campaigns/999

### Get all products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products

